## Critical Discovery: pigz Files Are Single-Member

**pigz output is single-member gzip.** pigz compresses blocks in parallel
but writes them into a SINGLE gzip stream, NOT separate gzip members. So
`silesia-pigz.gz`, `software-pigz.gz`, `logs-pigz.gz` are all single-member.

This means ALL 8 Tmax decompress losses (gzip AND pigz variants) have the
SAME root cause: no parallel single-member decompress.

